events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 25 points with 10 rebounds and nine assists to lead the Boston Celtics to a 118-105 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 25 points as Celtics cruise to 118-105 win over Knicks

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 30 points and the Golden State Warriors beat the Dallas Mavericks 126-102 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 30 points as Warriors beat Mavericks 126-102

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 29 points and 12 assists for his 16th double-double of the season, Aaron Nesmith scored a season-high 19, and the Indiana Pacers defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 129-111 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton's 16th double-double leads Pacers past Clippers 129-111

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 38 points, 12 assists and seven rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons extended their winning streak to a season-high six games with a 148-143 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham scores 38 as Pistons win 148-143 shootout over Hawks

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner and Anthony Black each scored 23 points, Paolo Banchero added 19 and the Orlando Magic pulled away in the second half to beat the Washington Wizards 110-90 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner and Anthony Black each score 23 points in the Magic's 110-90 win over the Wizards

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley, Chris Boucher,and RJ Barrett each scored 23 points and the Toronto Raptors made 20 3-pointers in a 127-109 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boucher has 23 points and 10 rebounds to help the Raptors beat slumping Suns 127-109

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 28 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo had 23 points and 16 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks used a strong fourth quarter to rally past the Miami Heat 120-113 on Sunday for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks finish strong to beat Heat 120-113 for 4th straight win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 22 points and nine rebounds and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame a 17-point deficit to beat the San Antonio Spurs 114-96 on Sunday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson powers the Pelicans to a 114-96 comeback victory over the Spurs

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 33 points, fellow All-Star Evan Mobley had 25 points, 13 rebounds and eight assists and the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 129-123 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 33 points, NBA-leading Cavaliers beat Grizzlies 129-123 for 7th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 37 points, eight rebounds, eight assists and three steals to help the West-leading Oklahoma City Thunder beat the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: West-leading Thunder outlast Timberwolves 130-123 behind 37 points from Gilgeous-Alexander
